cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper involves the analysis of hyperlink networks and ranking algorithms, which are commonly used in information retrieval and web search (cs.IR). It also involves the use of data mining techniques to extract people names and analyze their distributions (cs.DL). The study of cultural interactions and entanglements can be considered as a form of social network analysis (cs.SI). The analysis of geographical distributions and cross-cultural links can be related to spatial data analysis (cs.SD) and cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY).
